# Data Specification

## Purpose

This document defines the core data entities for CAP Market V1: what they are, the fields each one holds, and how they relate to each other. It is the reference every other specification and, eventually, every database/API design should point back to.

Only entities needed for the scope defined in PH-000 (Version Scope) and PH-003 (Customer Experience) are included. Entities for deferred features (loyalty, promotions, wholesale, supplier/farmer portals, barcode scanning, multi-branch, driver app) are intentionally excluded until those features are actually being built.

---

# Entity Overview

CAP Market V1 revolves around a simple chain:

```
Supplier Delivery → Inventory Lot → Packaging Batch → Product Stock → Order → Delivery/Pickup
```

Core entities:

- User
- Product
- Inventory Lot
- Packaging Batch
- Order
- Order Item
- Pricing Reason
- Delivery

---

# User

Represents anyone who logs into CAP Market — Customer, Employee, or Owner. A single entity with a role, rather than separate tables per role, since V1 has no need for role-specific fields beyond what's listed here.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | Unique, system-generated |
| phone_number | string | Used for OTP login; unique |
| name | string | |
| role | enum | `customer`, `employee`, `owner` |
| created_at | datetime | |

**Notes:**
- Authentication is phone number + OTP (see PH-003). No password is stored.
- Financial Hardship pricing (see Pricing Reason below) is based on the owner's personal knowledge of a customer's situation, not a field the customer self-reports.

---

# Product

Represents an item customers can order. V1 has a single product (Nakonde rice, 5 kg bags), but the entity is structured to support additional products as the business expands, per the "Abundant Produce" vision.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| name | string | e.g. "Nakonde Rice — 5kg Bag" |
| unit_size | string | e.g. "5kg" |
| base_price | decimal | Standard price before any Pricing Reason is applied (K150–K165 range currently) |
| is_active | boolean | Whether the product is currently orderable |

---

# Inventory Lot

Represents a bulk quantity of a product received from a supplier, before it's broken down into sellable units. Example: a 200kg bulk bag of Nakonde rice.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| product_id | reference | Links to Product |
| bulk_quantity_kg | decimal | e.g. 200 |
| cost | decimal | What CAP paid for this lot |
| received_date | date | |
| status | enum | `received`, `in_packaging`, `depleted` |

---

# Packaging Batch

Represents the event of converting an Inventory Lot into sellable retail units (e.g. breaking a 200kg bag into ~41 five-kg bags).

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| inventory_lot_id | reference | Links to the source Inventory Lot |
| product_id | reference | The resulting retail product |
| units_produced | integer | e.g. 41 |
| packaged_by | reference | Links to the Employee (User) who packaged it |
| packaged_date | date | |

**Notes:**
- Units produced from a Packaging Batch become available Product Stock (see below).

---

# Product Stock

Represents current sellable inventory for a Product — the running count of packaged units available to sell.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| product_id | reference | Links to Product |
| quantity_available | integer | Current count of sellable units |
| last_updated | datetime | |

**Notes:**
- Increases when a Packaging Batch completes.
- Decreases when an Order is placed (or confirmed, depending on business rule — to be defined in PH-006).

---

# Pricing Reason

Represents the discretionary reason a specific price was applied to a customer's order, as described in PH-000's Business Model Reality section.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| name | enum | `Referral`, `Delivery Assistance`, `Distribution Branch`, `Bulk Purchase`, `Financial Hardship`, `Standard` |
| description | string | Free text, optional |

**Notes:**
- Bulk Purchase tiers are not yet formalized (per PH-000) — V1 should allow this reason to be recorded without enforcing specific quantity thresholds.
- Financial Hardship is applied at the owner's discretion, not by any automated rule.
- The exact discount logic per reason belongs in PH-006 Business Rules, not here — this entity only records *which* reason applies.

---

# Order

Represents a customer's request to purchase one or more Products.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| customer_id | reference | Links to User (role = customer) |
| status | enum | `pending`, `confirmed`, `fulfilled`, `cancelled` |
| pricing_reason_id | reference | Links to Pricing Reason applied |
| total_price | decimal | Computed from Order Items |
| created_at | datetime | |

---

# Order Item

Represents a single product line within an Order. Separated from Order to support multiple products per order as the catalog grows beyond rice.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| order_id | reference | Links to Order |
| product_id | reference | Links to Product |
| quantity | integer | Number of units ordered |
| unit_price | decimal | Price applied to this line, after Pricing Reason |

---

# Delivery

Represents the fulfillment of an Order, whether by pickup or delivery. Per PH-003, coordination happens manually/outside the app for V1 — this entity exists to record status, not to power in-app scheduling.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| id | identifier | |
| order_id | reference | Links to Order |
| method | enum | `pickup`, `delivery` |
| status | enum | `pending`, `completed` |
| completed_date | date | Optional |

---

# Relationships Summary

- One **Inventory Lot** → many **Packaging Batches** (a lot may be packaged in stages)
- One **Packaging Batch** → one **Product** (increases its Product Stock)
- One **User** (customer) → many **Orders**
- One **Order** → many **Order Items**
- One **Order Item** → one **Product**
- One **Order** → one **Pricing Reason**
- One **Order** → one **Delivery**

---

# Deferred / Out of Scope for V1

Consistent with PH-000's Version Scope, the following are intentionally not modeled yet:

- Loyalty/points entities
- Promotions/coupon entities
- Wholesale customer or contract pricing entities
- Supplier or farmer portal entities (Inventory Lot currently assumes manual entry by staff, not a supplier-facing system)
- Barcode/SKU entities
- Multi-branch/location entities
- Driver-specific entities (Delivery is a simple status record, not a routing/assignment system)

